
Future Development
------------------

There are already plans to expand on the functionality
present in Karma.  Here's a list of some of the things I'm
working on for a future release.

--

o lynx browser support (no frames, no tables?)
o shorter ttl HTML tags so you don't have to click shift reload
o use file package instead of open
o standard perl install
o better perl docs (POD)
o configuration check tool (reads karma.conf file)
o pager/email alert support
o karmactl utility for 
  - starting karmad
  - stopping karmad
  - rereading the config file of karma
  - checking the status of a running karmad daemon
o web interface
  - using karmactl
  - editing karma.conf
o more services monitored
  - replication support
  - listener log monitor
  - trace/core file monitor
o karma.conf
  - specify frames/no frames/no tables support 
  - configure blinking/noblinking icons
